user.biography:
Fervor (noun): intense and passionate feeling. Tour the world with us.
🔻Apply for a feature:🔻

node.text:
How cute is Rasta? 🥰 Apply for a feature following the link in our bio and we will publish your photos in our account: @tourfervor

The adventure pup from Switzerland? Tag someone who loves @nature as him!
Photos and videos by @michelphotographych w/ @rastawhiteshepherd

Is this the most beautiful mantis in @nature? 🙏 Get your photos posted in our account, apply for a feature visiting tourfervor.com 👉🏼 the link is in our bio: @tourfervor

Flower mantises are those species of praying mantises that mimic flowers. Their coloration is an example of aggressive mimicry, a form of camouflage in which a predator's colours and patterns lure prey.

📽 @insecthaus_adi

Diving deep and free, just the water and me 😌 We can post your photos in our account, follow the link in our bio: @tourfervor and we will select your pictures

📽 @andrewdesloover w/ @bjgriffinmusic
📍Ginnie Springs, Florida

Ginnie Springs is in Gilchrist County about 6.5 miles (10.5 km) northwest of High Springs, Florida, USA. It is located on the south side of the Santa Fe River, to which it is connected. The water is clear and cold and there are accessible caverns with a sand and limestone bottom.

Ginnie Springs has been privately owned by the Wray family since 1971 and began functioning in 1976. In the mid-1990s when scuba diving grew in popularity, Bob Wray opened the springs to the public. The popularity of Ginnie took off and it became a nationally renowned diving spot which is still largely popular today.
